me":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"d79162d2-ea8d-55fd-836e-ea1ad829d735","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"47224ede-71c8-5986-90e0-aa7e07da9461","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"3e6e08a5-28f2-51f5-a9e0-4408814a4bed","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"d5b26a91-7f89-52f2-a6b2-b9373ef97515","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"c7ea2e16-11fc-593d-93d1-3e5925230b95","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},"subChapters":[{"id":"4bbe7f07-b62e-56ac-a22c-50170c857635","slug":"adrenocorticotrophic-hormone-stimulation-synacthenr-test","fullItemName":"Adrenocorticotrophic hormone stimulation (Synacthen®) test","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field e853bdb4-343a-4a0f-967e-55f3df9bd4b1 --><h3>Adrenocorticotrophic hormone stimulation (Synacthen®) test</h3><!-- end field e853bdb4-343a-4a0f-967e-55f3df9bd4b1 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 9045c3ee-7229-4903-aeff-a11ce58e63ee --><!-- begin field 90c13104-7280-493a-a035-50bdf81b169d --><ul><li class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>For the adrenocorticotrophic hormone (ACTH) stimulation (Synacthen<sup>®</sup>) test (in secondary care):</strong><ul><li>Blood samples are obtained to check serum cortisol levels before and 30 minutes after administering 250 micrograms of tetracosactide (a synthetic analogue of ACTH) intravenously or intramuscularly.</li><li>This test can be performed at any time of day, as the post-stimulation value is used for diagnostic purposes.</li></ul></li><li><strong>A normal response to the ACTH stimulation test is an increase in the serum cortisol level.</strong><ul><li>In people with normal adrenal reserve, cortisol levels increase to more than 500–550 nanomol/L after 30 or 60 minutes.</li><li>In people with adrenal insufficiency, serum cortisol levels do not increase adequately in response to tetracosactide because the adrenal cortex is already receiving maximum stimulation from endogenous ACTH.</li></ul></li></ul><p class=\"MsoNormal\">[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/addisons-disease/references/\">Arlt, 2003</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/addisons-disease/references/\">Bornstein, 2009</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/addisons-disease/references/\">Vaidya, 2009</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/addisons-disease/references/\">Wallace, 2009</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/addisons-disease/references/\">Chakera, 2010</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/addisons-disease/references/\">Husebye, 2014</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/addisons-disease/references/\">Bancos, 2015</a>]</p><!-- end field 90c13104-7280-493a-a035-50bdf81b169d --><!-- end item 9045c3ee-7229-4903-aeff-a11ce58e63ee -->","subChapters":[]},{"id":"e4923a0b-3c36-54cf-abe4-6f690364d62d","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-d5f","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 8b8967d8-8f1e-4cf2-adf6-cc72f8d739bd --><h3>Basis for recommendation</h3><!-- end field 8b8967d8-8f1e-4cf2-adf6-cc72f8d739bd -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item d5fd6211-c1db-4b98-b434-b0de4e5ed2ef --><!-- begin field 9f50ea4a-9f32-4eef-bd56-28eed3eb7cdd --><h4>Confirmation of the diagnosis of Addison's disease in secondary care</h4><ul><li>The Addison's Clinical Advisory Panel recommend that confirmation of diagnosis of Addison's disease should take place in secondary care [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/addisons-disease/references/\">Addison’s Disease Clinical Advisory Panel, 2020b</a>].</li></ul><h4>Secondary care investigations</h4><ul><li>The adrenocorticotrophic hormone (ACTH) stimulation (Synacthen<sup>®</sup>) test is widely recommended in clinical guidance and review articles [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/addisons-disease/references/\">Wallace, 2009</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/addisons-disease/references/\">Husebye, 2014</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/addisons-disease/references/\">Bancos, 2015</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/addisons-disease/references/\">Burton, 2015</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/addisons-disease/references/\">Bornstein, 2016</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/addisons-disease/references/\">Reznik, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/addisons-disease/references/\">Addison’s Disease Clinical Advisory Panel, 2020b</a>] to confirm the diagnosis of Addison’s disease.</li><li>Information on other investigations that may be carried out in secondary care to confirm Addison’s disease and identify a cause is based on expert opinion in clinical guidance and review articles [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/addisons-disease/references/\">Wallace, 2009</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/addisons-disease/references/\">Husebye, 2014</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/addisons-disease/references/\">Bancos, 2015</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/addisons-disease/references/\">Bornstein, 2016</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/addisons-disease/references/\">Bowden, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/addisons-disease/references/\">BMJ Best Practice, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/addisons-disease/references/\">Addison’s Disease Clinical Advisory Panel, 2020b</a>].</li></ul><!-- end field 9f50ea4a-9f32-4eef-bd56-28eed3eb7cdd --><!-- end item d5fd6211-c1db-4b98-b434-b0de4e5ed2ef -->","subChapters":[]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}